          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "1tish",
          "text": "Step 1: Start with a working OpenClaw install",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "8jgka",
          "text": "Before you do anything with clawchief, make sure OpenClaw itself is already installed and working.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [
            {
              "length": 3,
              "offset": 13,
              "style": "Bold"
            },
            {
              "length": 28,
              "offset": 53,
              "style": "Bold"
            }
          ],
          "key": "e0vrj",
          "text": "clawchief is not a replacement for OpenClaw.\nIt’s an operating layer on top of it.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "3d0ad",
          "text": "Step 2: Get GOG working first",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "a4deb",
          "text": "This setup expects gog to work for:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "fhgvo",
          "text": "Gmail message search",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "7refv",
          "text": "Calendar list and event reads",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bdlg",
          "text": "Google Sheets metadata reads",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "700ou",
          "text": "Google Docs reads (if you want meeting-notes ingestion)",
          "type": "unordered-list-item"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "25i8a",
          "text": "If those are broken, your assistant won’t be able to do real executive-assistant work reliably.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "96rkl",
          "text": "Step 3: Install the skills",
          "type": "header-two"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "ae294",
          "text": "Copy these skill directories into ~/.openclaw/skills/",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [
            {
              "key": 3,
              "length": 1,
              "offset": 0
            }
          ],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "cds0b",
          "text": " ",
          "type": "atomic"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "dgt4i",
          "text": "These are the behavioral building blocks.",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "bbidf",
          "text": "They teach OpenClaw how to:",
          "type": "unstyled"
        },
        {
          "data": [],
          "entityRanges": [],
          "inlineStyleRanges": [],
          "key": "f1f8h",
          "text": "act like an executive assistant",
